    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tubular trade beads of West Africa, known from the 15th century, of different and variegated colors though the most highly prized were blue with a greenish translucence. Their manufacture and component material is uncertain.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Comercio de cuentas tubulares de África del Este, conocidas desde el siglo 15, de colores diferentes y abigarrados, aunque las más altamente cotizadas son azules con una traslucidez verdosa. Su elaboración y materiales componentes son desconocidos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Buisvormige handelskralen uit West-Afrika, bekend sinds de 15de eeuw, met verschillende en bont geschakeerde kleuren. De waardevolste waren blauw met een groenachtige schijn. Het fabricaat en het materiaal van de componenten is onbekend.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>西非地區的管狀交易串珠，自十五世紀為人所知，有不同的顏色交錯，其中最珍貴的是帶有半透明綠的藍色串珠。製作過程與成分原料不定。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
